    "investigated the idea that we should train the critic until it reaches the best level because EM distance is continuous and can be changed.",
    "Since Wasserstein is almost always differentiable, it is thought that the more a critic learns, the more stable the Wasserstein gradient will be.",
    "When the discriminator uses JS divergence, it gets more accurate and stable gradients.",
    "However, the real gradient is 0 because JS is locally saturated, which makes gradients disappear.",
    "The observation is that you can get a reliable Wasserstein gradient by practicing it over and over."
